===Pronunciation===
vall·ey

*IPA: /væl.li/ 
*SAMPA: /v{l.li/ 
*AHD: /vălē/ 

===Etymology===

F ''vallée'' fr. L ''vales''

===Noun===
'''valley''' (plural: valleys)

#An [[elongated]] [[depression]] between  [[hill]]s or [[mountain]]s, often with a [[river]] flowing through it.
#The area which drains into a river.
#Any [[structure]] resembling 1, eg the meeting point of two [[pitch]]ed [[roof]]s.

